cards.title: Jalna Student Suicide: 13-Year-Old's Death Sparks Debate on School Harassment and Rising Cases
cards.abstract: This special report covers the tragic death of a 13-year-old student in Jalna, Maharashtra, who died by suicide after jumping from her school building. The incident has brought national attention to the issue of student well-being, with the victim's father alleging mental torture by school teachers. The report contextualises this event with other recent cases in Jaipur and Delhi, highlighting a distressing trend. According to the report, 'the priority remains to ensure another bright mind is not lost to suicide'. It cites National Crime Records Bureau (NCRB) data, which shows student suicides increased from 8,423 in 2013 to 13,892 in 2023, a rise of about 65% in a decade. The programme raises the question of whether schools are solely responsible or if parents also have a role to play in preventing such tragedies.

images.title: Popular names of 2025: The sweetest meanings behind the top names
images.caption: Away from all the books and Excel sheets, doomscrolling might be one of the side effects of finding the perfect name for the young child. However, in the middle of all the chaos, some timeless classics might bring the bloom with the perfect energy and charm in the family – the names that suit the grace and regality. Shining in the confident light, a fine share of baby names have been celestially favorite among the new parents of 2025, as BabyCenter has released the list of popular ones. So, here’s the list of the sweetest meanings behind the popular baby names!

images.title: ​Olivia
images.caption: Stemmed from the olive tree, Olivia suggests peace and endurance. The name, which grabbed the attention after being part of William Shakespeare’s ‘Twelfth Night,’ highlights the strong-minded strength backed by great compassion. For parents naming their child ‘Olivia,’ the word raises the perfect opportunity to raise the dreamers. Derived from Latin, the name has been given shout-out by One Direction – so, it’s literally the perfect name ever!

images.title: ​Amelia
images.caption: Derived from German roots, Amelia is a name that has been favored by a long line of royals. The exquisite name suggests hardworking, celebrating courage, and ambition. For the parents naming their child ‘Amelia,’ the word represents the hope of soaring high without any fear, and the determination of pursuits. While the name has many variations with different accents, it recently gained popularity after decades, even in masculine versions as well.

images.title: ​Aurora
images.caption: Oh, the time when the sky looks the most beautiful – dawn. With the prolific meaning of new beginnings and imagination, Aurora shines the light with optimism. For the parents naming their child ‘Aurora,’ the word transcends mundane with a celestial feel and radiant energy. Derived from Latin, the name is the perfect example of timeless appeal.
